About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have aging parents and bought this as a gift. They are getting to the age where they needed suitcases that were easily maneuverable. They reported to me that they were shocked at how much storage space each of the suit cases had. They took their large cases on a road trip and said they loved them.As of October 2023, they have also used them while flying. And anyone who knows how baggage is handled at the airports, know that you often find yourself nervous for the state of your luggage. Their luggage held up great and the contents inside barely shifted, even with the expected neglect that is sometimes wrought by the workers and machines.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These look really good in person. Awesome shade of blue. The handles feel a bit flimsy, but they do hold up. Case feels durable. I love it,

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great suitcase set!
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this set of Rockland Melbourne Hardside Expandable Spinner Wheel Luggage in a beautiful Navy Blue for my teenage son. The 2-Piece Set came in the carry-on travel size of 20 inch and a larger 28 inch. They aren't as lightweight as they could be. They spin well and aren't glitchy in their movement. The handles could be a better design, but not a dealbreaker. The suitcase shell texture is nice, and we are hoping it helps in recognizing his bags on the baggage carousel. Got these for less than $140 which is a great price for a two-piece set of luggage. We will see how durable they are after a summer of travel by a teenager.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars So far so good, but will it last?
reviews.reviewText: I used the large one for a recent trip to visit family. I packed this bad boy full of christmas gifts. I didn't have any trouble with the suitcase, but the exterior has a little more give than I would like for a "hard" sided suitcase. I'm skeptical, but we shall see. I don't anticipate the big one getting used all that often, but the smaller will probably get used several times a year. We shall see! I like the color, the blue is nice and I was able to easily identify my new bag at the airport. Super lightweight when empty. The wheels work great, very smooth and easy to twirl around. The telescoping handle is rock solid, something I find many bags skimp on. Not this one!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Sturdy, love the inside, and didn't scratch up when traveling, roll easily.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Painfully difficult to use, very frustrating
reviews.reviewText: I am most disappointed in this set of suitcases. The side-carry handles are on the wrong half of the suitcase, they should be on the side that has the inside zipper closure so that when you go to close the suitcase everything doesn't fall out because it's only help in by thin straps. They were flimsy when trying to line the sides up to zip closed as well. Additionally, the handle used to roll the suitcase didn't lock on the smaller case and the wheels on either case were difficult to maintain a good steady roll when walking thru the airport. I bought these in October for my 1st trip abroad (in March) and had no reason to use them prior to this trip. Suppossedly it is too late to return them...but I think there should be exceptions. How does one know without using them, how they will work...only getting 1 painfully difficult use out of them does not seem rightl

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for price!
reviews.reviewText: We bought these for my business trip to Los Angeles. I was nervous about the sizes but decided on using the largest one to fit all of my stuff. It held everything I needed and then some! The space is great and it feels really good quality for the price. I would recommend for first time fliers to get a bright color or something that stands out. Black is very common and hard to find at baggage claim, LOL. They roll really well and did the job. I love the different size options, and the smallest counts as a carry on with Delta! I love these and think they will last a really long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love these!! They fit everything we could think to take on vacation and then some! Tons of room in both of these. Definitely suggest buying a luggage scale because you can exceed 50lbs pretty quickly!

reviews.reviewTitle: We purchased 6 sets of suitcases. 1 came in damaged.
reviews.reviewText: The colours are wonderful - I wanted 6 individual options for each family member so I loved that there were more choices to choose from. We bought 6 sets (28 & 21 inch) and so far they look great. I’ll update review after our trip to see how well they’re built. reviews.reviewText: I like these cases. The coral colour is distinctive which helps to spot them on the conveyer at airports. They are practical, roomy and stood up to a multi-stop trip to and about Mexico from Canada. There are no built-in compartments and partitions in them which I prefer..
